text: Employment Agreement Position Employee shall serve in the role defined in Exhibit A
Compensation Employer shall pay the employee a salary according to company policy
Non I Compete Employee agrees not to engage in competing business for one year post I employment
Governing Law This agreement is governed by the laws of the applicable jurisdiction.
SaaS Subscription Agreement License Grant Customer is granted a non I exclusive, non I transferable right to access the service
Uptime Commitment Provider guarantees 99.5% monthly uptime
Data Security Provider will implement industry I standard security controls
Termination Either party may terminate with 30 days written notice.
Mutual Non I Disclosure Agreement Purpose This Mutual Non I Disclosure Agreement outlines confidentiality obligations between the parties
Confidentiality Each party agrees to protect all confidential information using reasonable measures
Term This agreement remains in effect for three years from the effective date
Liability Neither party shall be liable for indirect or consequential damages.
Master Services Agreement Scope of Work The provider agrees to deliver professional services as outlined in attached statements of work
Payment Terms Client shall remit payment within 30 days of invoice receipt
Warranties Provider warrants services will be performed in a professional manner
Indemnification Each party agrees to indemnify the other against losses arising from negligence or misconduct.
Commercial Lease Agreement Premises Landlord leases the commercial premises to the tenant
Rent Tenant agrees to pay monthly rent as specified in Schedule A
Maintenance Tenant shall maintain the premises in good condition
Liability Tenant assumes responsibility for damages resulting from misuse.
